					<item>
		<title><![CDATA[5G - Công nghệ 5G]]></title>
		<link>https://annk.info/?p=561</link>
		<pubDate></pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://annk.info/?p=561</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[The next technology trend that follows the IoT is 5G. Where 3G and 4G technologies have enabled us to browse the internet, use data driven services, increased bandwidths for streaming on Spotify or YouTube and so much more, 5G services are expected to revolutionize our lives. by enabling services that rely on advanced technologies like AR and VR, alongside cloud based gaming services like Google Stadia, NVidia GeForce Now and much more. It is expected to be used in factories, HD cameras that help improve safety and traffic management, smart grid control and smart retail too.

Related learning: <a title="How 5G Technology Will Change the World" href="https://www.simplilearn.com/how-5g-technology-will-change-the-world-article" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How 5G Technology Will Change the World</a>?

Just about every telecom company like Verizon, Tmobile, Apple, Nokia Corp, QualComm, are now working on creating 5G applications. 5G Network subscriptions will reach <a title="4.4 billion by the end of 2027" href="https://www.ericsson.com/en/reports-and-papers/mobility-report/dataforecasts/mobile-subscriptions-outlook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">4.4 billion by the end of 2027</a>, making it an emerging technology trend you must watch out for, and also save a spot in.]]></content:encoded>
