					<item>
		<title><![CDATA[Tips for upgrading your computer hardware]]></title>
		<link>https://annk.info/?p=582</link>
		<pubDate></pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://annk.info/?p=582</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="headline basecomponent parbase">
<h2>Upgrades to get the most out of your gaming PC</h2>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">

If your gaming computer is running slowly, has long load times, shows screen tearing, lag or other artifacts, you could be wondering what you need to upgrade on your PC. It’s likely that your hardware could be to blame. If it's been a while since you bought a new computer or upgraded the components, it might be time to take a look at what's available now and what could improve your gaming. Follow these steps for the best gaming PC upgrades to ensure you get the most out of your hardware.

</div>
<div class="anchor basecomponent parbase"></div>
<div class="headline basecomponent parbase">
<h3>Step 1: Install RAM</h3>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">

If you’re having difficulty loading pages, live streaming, or switching among applications, one gaming PC upgrade to consider is increasing or replacing your <a href="https://www.crucial.com/articles/for-gamers/how-much-ram-for-gaming">computer memory (RAM)</a>. RAM stores data that is currently being used. Many games store textures and maps in RAM.

Most factory-built computers have slots to add more memory modules. If there isn’t room for more modules, you can replace existing memory with larger-capacity modules.

The <a href="https://www.crucial.com/store/advisor">Crucial® Advisor™ tool</a> or <a href="https://www.crucial.com/store/systemscanner">System Scanner tool</a> can tell you which memory modules are compatible with your computer.

<a href="https://www.crucial.com/articles/about-memory/how-to-upgrade-desktop-memory">Find out how to install memory in your desktop computer.</a>

</div>
<div class="container basecomponent parbase">
<div class=" margin-bottom--small">
<div class="container-content   top-left auto-dismiss
          " data-toggler="" data-animate="fade-in fade-out" data-closable="" aria-expanded="true" data-b="6kpzl1-b">
<div class="row">
<div class="columns small-12">
<div class="image basecomponent parbase is-maxwidthed">
<div id="zurbrow_copy_copyzurbcolumn2contentcontainercontainerContentcontainercontainerContentimage" class="imagewidth-attributes"><img id="1glrba-interchange" title="install memory modules" src="https://www.crucial.com/content/dam/ballistix/dram-products/sport-series/ddr4/sport-at/images/ballistix-asus-sport-at-computer-build/050819-Ballistix-ASUS-SportAT-Computer-Build-Image-008.PSD.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg" alt="install memory modules" data-interchange="[/content/dam/ballistix/dram-products/sport-series/ddr4/sport-at/images/ballistix-asus-sport-at-computer-build/050819-Ballistix-ASUS-SportAT-Computer-Build-Image-008.PSD.transform/small-jpg/img.jpg, small], [/content/dam/ballistix/dram-products/sport-series/ddr4/sport-at/images/ballistix-asus-sport-at-computer-build/050819-Ballistix-ASUS-SportAT-Computer-Build-Image-008.PSD.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg, medium]" data-resize="1glrba-interchange" data-b="0qmavd-b" /></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="anchor basecomponent parbase"></div>
<div class="headline basecomponent parbase">
<h3>Step 2: Upgrade storage</h3>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">

If your current storage drive is nearly full or if it is just too slow and you're experiencing freezing or hangs, upgrade it. If you have a traditional hard drive (HDD), this is a good time to look into a solid state drive (SSD). SSDs start up faster and are more reliable and durable than HDDs. SSDs run at a higher speed, and allow the entire system to run more efficient because the other components are not waiting for data like they do when using a HDD.

<a href="https://www.crucial.com/articles/for-gamers/the-best-ssd-for-gaming">Read more about SSDs for gaming.</a>

Compare the current capacity of your storage drive with newer models. Both hard drives and solid state drive manufacturers are always increasing the storage capacity of drives. You can get a faster drive with more storage space relatively cheaply.

The Crucial® Advisor™ tool or System Scanner tool can tell you which SSDs are compatible with your computer.

<a href="https://www.crucial.com/articles/about-ssd/how-to-install-solid-state-drive">Read more about installing a SSD.</a>

</div>
<div class="container basecomponent parbase">
<div class=" margin-bottom--small">
<div class="container-content   top-left auto-dismiss
          " data-toggler="" data-animate="fade-in fade-out" data-closable="" aria-expanded="true" data-b="9j0cws-b">
<div class="row">
<div class="columns small-12">
<div class="image basecomponent parbase is-maxwidthed">
<div id="zurbrow_copy_copyzurbcolumn2contentcontainercontainerContentcontainer_1073412807containerContentimage_405198256" class="imagewidth-attributes"><img id="e1z7or-interchange" title="upgrade storage" src="https://www.crucial.com/content/dam/crucial/brand-assets/photography/lifestyle/installation/crucial-laptop-installation-kitchen-51.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg" alt="upgrade storage" data-interchange="[/content/dam/crucial/brand-assets/photography/lifestyle/installation/crucial-laptop-installation-kitchen-51.jpg.transform/small-jpg/img.jpg, small], [/content/dam/crucial/brand-assets/photography/lifestyle/installation/crucial-laptop-installation-kitchen-51.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg, medium]" data-resize="e1z7or-interchange" data-b="bc24wx-b" /></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="anchor basecomponent parbase"></div>
<div class="headline basecomponent parbase">
<h3>Step 3: Upgrade graphics card</h3>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">

If you're having trouble with lag, freezing graphics, or screen tearing, consider upgrading your graphics card. Unless a computer is built specifically for gaming, manufacturers will frequently put in a low-end graphics card. If the rest of your computer is functioning well, a graphics card upgrade can really improve your gaming experience.

</div>
<div class="container basecomponent parbase">
<div class=" margin-bottom--small">
<div class="container-content   top-left auto-dismiss
          " data-toggler="" data-animate="fade-in fade-out" data-closable="" aria-expanded="true" data-b="b9t00x-b">
<div class="row">
<div class="columns small-12">
<div class="image basecomponent parbase is-maxwidthed">
<div id="zurbrow_copy_copyzurbcolumn2contentcontainercontainerContentcontainer_983448103containerContentimage_1927881043" class="imagewidth-attributes"><img id="x7ypy7-interchange" title="upgrade graphics card" src="https://www.crucial.com/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_1164881479.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg" alt="upgrade graphics card" data-interchange="[/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_1164881479.jpg.transform/small-jpg/img.jpg, small], [/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_1164881479.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg, medium]" data-resize="x7ypy7-interchange" data-b="8met8l-b" /></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="anchor basecomponent parbase"></div>
<div class="headline basecomponent parbase">
<h3>Step 4: Upgrade the processor</h3>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">

Although upgrading your processor (CPU) can improve the efficiency of your computer, it can be quite involved. You need to make sure that your motherboard and memory are compatible with the new processor, or replace everything at the same time. Also, check that your current cooling system will accommodate the upgraded CPU. To determine if a processor upgrade will help your computer, there are a variety of third-party benchmark tests you can run. These tests will indicate if your CPU is underpowered. If you’re considering upgrading your processor, you might want to get a new system instead.

</div>
<div class="container basecomponent parbase">
<div class=" margin-bottom--small">
<div class="container-content   top-left auto-dismiss
          " data-toggler="" data-animate="fade-in fade-out" data-closable="" aria-expanded="true" data-b="3blaew-b">
<div class="row">
<div class="columns small-12">
<div class="image basecomponent parbase is-maxwidthed">
<div id="zurbrow_copy_copyzurbcolumn2contentcontainercontainerContentcontainer_101902657containerContentimage_701513686" class="imagewidth-attributes"><img id="32hp29-interchange" title="Upgrade the processor" src="https://www.crucial.com/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_1267530541.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg" alt="Upgrade the processor" data-interchange="[/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_1267530541.jpg.transform/small-jpg/img.jpg, small], [/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_1267530541.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg, medium]" data-resize="32hp29-interchange" data-b="s4seeb-b" /></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="anchor basecomponent parbase"></div>
<div class="headline basecomponent parbase">
<h3>Step 5: Upgrade the peripherals</h3>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">

Another way to give your PC gaming a boost is to upgrade your peripherals. If you’re using an older monitor, a new one can improve visibility in games.

A gaming mouse and keyboard can make a big difference in your play. If you’re using a standard mouse and keyboard, upgrading to gaming-specific tools can enhance your play.

It’s not hard to upgrade some of your computer hardware and it can make a big difference in the speed and responsiveness of your system.

</div>
<div class="container basecomponent parbase">
<div class=" margin-bottom--small">
<div class="container-content   top-left auto-dismiss
          " data-toggler="" data-animate="fade-in fade-out" data-closable="" aria-expanded="true" data-b="c4sch8-b">
<div class="row">
<div class="columns small-12">
<div class="image basecomponent parbase is-maxwidthed">
<div id="zurbrow_copy_copyzurbcolumn2contentcontainercontainerContentcontainer_1081089429containerContentimage_612446137" class="imagewidth-attributes"><img id="3yrj8g-interchange" title="Upgrade the peripherals" src="https://www.crucial.com/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_478630630.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg" alt="Upgrade the peripherals" data-interchange="[/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_478630630.jpg.transform/small-jpg/img.jpg, small], [/content/dam/crucial/articles/for-gamers/new026-how-to-upgrade-a-gaming-pc/shutterstock_478630630.jpg.transform/medium-jpg/img.jpg, medium]" data-resize="3yrj8g-interchange" data-b="fkpcqs-b" /></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">

If you’re looking for the best upgrades for your gaming PC, Crucial has a wide range of memory and SSDs to suit all needs. Take a look at our products section and upgrade your PC hardware with the memory and storage experts.

</div>]]></content:encoded>
