		<title><![CDATA[[ENG] How to check process start time on Windows]]></title>
		<link>https://annk.info/eng-how-to-check-process-start-time-on-windows/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 19 Apr 2019 09:15:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://annk.info/eng-how-to-check-process-start-time-on-windows/</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #111111; font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 2.5rem; font-style: italic; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 35px; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: rgba(0 , 0 , 0 , 0.8); font-size: 21px;">This article will guide you how to install &amp; check process start time on Windows operating system.</span></div><ul style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin: 0px 0px 28px 35px; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: inherit; list-style-type: disc;">Download Process Explorer from Microsoft download page</li></ul><pre style="background-color: #f5f2f0; border-radius: 5px; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: &quot;operator mono ssm a&quot;, &quot;operator mono ssm b&quot;, &quot;source code pro&quot;, Menlo, Consolas, Monaco, monospace; font-size: 16px; overflow-wrap: normal; overflow: scroll auto; padding: 1.5rem; resize: both; word-break: normal;"><a href="https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/bb896653.aspx" rel="nofollow noopener" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: 1px dotted rgb(255, 78, 0); box-sizing: inherit; color: #ff4e00; text-decoration-line: none; transition: background-color 0.25s ease-in 0s, border-color 0s ease-in 0s, transform 0.75s cubic-bezier(0.44, 0.51, 0.24, 0.99) 0s, box-shadow 1s cubic-bezier(0.44, 0.51, 0.24, 0.99) 0s;" target="_blank">http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/bb896653.aspx</a></pre><ul style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin: 0px 0px 28px 35px; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: inherit; list-style-type: disc;">Extract the downloaded zip file</li></ul><div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin-bottom: 28px; padding: 0px;">Now, you are ready to use Process Explorer</div><ul style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin: 0px 0px 28px 35px; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: inherit; list-style-type: disc;">Double click &nbsp;open it, it will look like below</li></ul><div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin-bottom: 28px; padding: 0px;"><img alt="" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20525" height="605" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" src="https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp.png" srcset="https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp.png 800w, https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp-349x264.png 349w" style="border-style: none; box-sizing: inherit; height: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; max-width: 100%;" width="800" /></div><ul style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin: 0px 0px 28px 35px; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: inherit; list-style-type: disc;">Click on View &gt;&gt; Select Columns</li><li style="box-sizing: inherit; list-style-type: disc;">Click on Process Performance tab and select Start Time</li><li style="box-sizing: inherit; list-style-type: disc;">Click on Ok</li></ul><div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin-bottom: 28px; padding: 0px;"><img alt="" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20526" height="569" sizes="(max-width: 454px) 100vw, 454px" src="https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp-view-column.png" srcset="https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp-view-column.png 454w, https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp-view-column-211x264.png 211w" style="border-style: none; box-sizing: inherit; height: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; max-width: 100%;" width="454" /></div><ul style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin: 0px 0px 28px 35px; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: inherit; list-style-type: disc;">You will notice additional column is added called Start Time in Process Explorer.</li></ul><div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin-bottom: 28px; padding: 0px;"><img alt="" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20527" height="599" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" src="https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp-start-time.png" srcset="https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp-start-time.png 800w, https://geekflare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/processxp-start-time-353x264.png 353w" style="border-style: none; box-sizing: inherit; height: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; max-width: 100%;" width="800" /></div><div style="background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: charter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 21px; margin-bottom: 28px; padding: 0px;">I hope this helps you in your application troubleshooting procedure.</div>]]></content:encoded>
